<law type="statute"><section><amendatorysection chaptername="Cities Of The First Class" statutenumber="16-316" amended="yes"><bookinfo>Revised Statutes Supplement, 2019</bookinfo><statuteno>16-316</statuteno><catchline>Mayor; pardons; remission of fines.</catchline><para>The mayor of a city of the first class shall have power after conviction to remit fines and forfeitures, and to grant reprieves and pardons for all offenses arising under the ordinances of the city.</para></amendatorysection></section><source><para>Laws 1901, c. 18, &#167; 23, p. 235; </para><para>R.S.1913, &#167; 4882; </para><para>C.S.1922, &#167; 4050; </para><para>C.S.1929, &#167; 16-312; </para><para>R.S.1943, &#167; 16-316; </para><para>Laws 2019, LB194, &#167; 10. </para><effectivedate>September 1, 2019</effectivedate></source></law>
